250 g Ground Turkey
340 g Pizza Dough
7 g Chives
2 unit(s) Sour Cream
56 g Green Cabbage, shredded
1 unit(s) Carrot
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
1 tsp Dill-Garlic Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Egg
1 tbsp Oil*
2 tbsp All-Purpose Flour*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Sprinkle both sides of dough with flour. With floured hands, divide dough into 2 equal pieces (4 pieces for 4 ppl) on a well-floured surface.
Stretch each piece of dough into a 5-x8-inch round or oval shape.
Set aside to rest on a parchment-lined baking sheet, 8-10 min. (NOTE: Use 2 baking sheets for 4 ppl).

Peel, then grate carrot.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Whisk together egg and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water together in a small bowl. Set aside. (NOTE: This is your egg wash for the outside of the piroshki.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey, cabbage, onions and carrot. Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Add vinegar, garlic, Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and Dill Garlic Spice Belnd and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside to cool slightly, 5 min.

With floured hands, stretch dough again into large oval shapes. (NOTE: The dough should now hold its shape.)
Using a slotted spoon, top one half of each piroshki with turkey mixture.
Fold over dough over filling, then crimp edges to seal.
Brush egg wash over each piroshki, then make one small slit on the top of each piroshki using a knife.

Bake piroshkis in the middle of the oven until golden-brown, 18-22 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, bake in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, thinly slice chives.
Add sour cream and chives to another small bowl. Season with salt, then stir to combine.
Allow piroshkis to cool slightly before serving, 3-4 min.
Divide piroshkis between plates and cut in half, if desired.
Serve chive sour cream alongside for dipping.

If you've opted to get turkey, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to the pan, then add turkey and vegetables. Cook turkey in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef.**